config CRC_ALIF
	bool "Alif Ensemble CRC engine (ADR 0017 Tier-1.5 clean-room, BENCH-UNVERIFIED)"
	default y
	depends on CRC_DRIVER
	depends on DT_HAS_ALIF_CRC_ENABLED
	select CRC_DRIVER_HAS_CRC8_CCITT
	select CRC_DRIVER_HAS_CRC16
	select CRC_DRIVER_HAS_CRC16_CCITT
	select CRC_DRIVER_HAS_CRC32_C
	select CRC_DRIVER_HAS_CRC32_IEEE
	help
	  Alif Ensemble hardware CRC engine class driver (compatible "alif,crc"),
	  implementing the UPSTREAM Zephyr v4.4 CRC class API
	  (<zephyr/drivers/crc.h>: crc_begin / crc_update / crc_finish over
	  struct crc_ctx).  CLEAN-ROOM, NOT vendored: the Apache-2.0 zephyr_alif
	  fork's CRC driver targets a fork-private API (crc_compute() +
	  struct crc_params, CONFIG_CRC_DRV) that does not exist upstream and so
	  cannot be consumed verbatim -- the register model is re-authored
	  value-only from the Alif DFP (drivers/include/crc.h + soc.h), with the
	  programming sequence cross-checked against the fork CMSIS Driver_CRC.c.

	  Polled, memory-mapped block (no interrupt, no DMA used by the driver),
	  so it pulls in NO hal_alif library (like flash_mram_alif).  Maps the
	  upstream enum crc_type onto the engine's CRC_8_CCITT / CRC_16 /
	  CRC_16_CCITT / CRC_32 / CRC_32C algorithms; other types return -ENOTSUP.
	  On the E8 SoM this binds crc0@48107000 / crc1@48108000.  Not
	  silicon-validated.  ADR 0017 Tier-1.5 (in-tree-thin over the silicon;
	  there is no Tier-2 fork path to retire onto).  Task #21.
	  Driver: zephyr/drivers/crc/crc_alif.c.

