# Alif Ensemble CAMERA CAPTURE path (CPI controller + DesignWare MIPI CSI-2
# bridge + DesignWare MIPI D-PHY + ON Semi ARX3A0 sensor) -- ADR 0017 Tier-2,
# vendored from the Apache-2.0 zephyr_alif fork.  Upstream Zephyr v4.4 +
# hal_alif ship NONE of these (no CPI/CSI video drivers, no mipi_dphy class),
# so they are carried in-tree so they survive a `west update` (the ADC_ALIF /
# MHUv2 precedents).
#
# The fork video drivers originally implemented the OLDER Zephyr video API
# whose callbacks took `enum video_endpoint_id ep` -- a type upstream v4.4
# REMOVED in the video-API rework (v4.4 callbacks are (dev, fmt) / (dev, caps) /
# (dev, enable, type) / (dev, cid)).  The video drivers have now been PORTED to
# the v4.4 API by Alp Lab AB (each API-shim change is marked at its call site;
# see the per-driver provenance headers); the former ALP_VIDEO_ALIF_BROKEN gate
# is RETIRED and the driver TUs build in directly when their DT node is enabled.
# Runtime capture stays HW-blocked on this batch (no camera sensor wired).
# vendor-ext, BENCH-UNVERIFIED.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
