	  and don't write to it from firmware.

config ALP_SDK_CHIP_PI3DBS12212
	bool "Diodes PI3DBS12212A 2:1 differential mux (GPIO-only)"
	depends on GPIO
	help
	  Compile chips/pi3dbs12212/pi3dbs12212.c.  Drives the
	  passive 12 Gbps differential mux on V2N-M1 that switches
	  PCIe routing between DEEPX (on-module) and the E1M edge
	  connector.  GPIO-only -- no I2C surface.  Driver takes
	  two alp_gpio_t handles (PD on Renesas P80, SEL on P95
	  per V2N-M1 wiring) and exposes a 3-state model:
	  OFF / PATH_0 / PATH_1, with glitch-free PD pulse on
	  path-to-path transitions.

